                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">jinxer</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;05/05/2003&nbsp;: 5:03:07 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Kerhunge great guide.  I love location #6.  Never any one else there.  If there is a group at RCY just let them know you are there and I never had a problem.  In fact, because I would pull nonSKs as my first choice, if there was a group in RCY it would help me out.  Less SKs to deal with and fewer mobs that will add on pulls.  Now the SKs are quiet doable, but the risk vs reward isn't there.  <br /><br />I have noticed that the point where the mob will turn and stop to fight seems to be a function of your current HPs, and not percentage like I thought it would be.  I have 2200 self buffed and if im at 1800 or so the mob would stop at 11% of its health.  If I was under 1800 it would stop at 7% and if I was 1000 or so it wouldn't stop until 3%.  Also once I was buffed from a raid and had 4100, when I had 3500 HPs at the end of the fight the mob would stop at 19%.  This really helped my mana recovery as I could sit for much longer periods at the end of the fight.  Hope this helps out.</span></font></td>
              </tr>
